            <h1>Understanding Shii Jurisprudence in Contemporary Context</h1>
            <p class="event-date">March 15, 2025 • 2:00 PM GMT</p>
            
            <div class="event-page-content">
                <div class="event-abstract">
                    <h2>Abstract</h2>
                    <p>This presentation explores the dynamic relationship between traditional Shii jurisprudence (fiqh) and contemporary legal and social challenges. Drawing from both classical sources and modern scholarly discourse, we examine how Shii jurists have adapted age-old legal principles to address current issues such as medical ethics, environmental concerns, and social justice.</p>
                    
                    <p>The discussion will focus on key methodological approaches employed by contemporary Shii scholars, including the role of reason (aql) in legal reasoning, the application of general principles (qawa'id), and the concept of changing circumstances (taghayyur al-ahwal). We will analyze specific case studies that demonstrate how these methodological tools have been utilized to derive legal opinions on modern issues.</p>
                    
                    <p>Furthermore, this presentation will examine the institutional frameworks within which contemporary Shii jurisprudence operates, including the role of religious authorities (maraji') and the process of legal consultation (istifta'). The discussion will conclude with an analysis of future challenges and opportunities for Shii jurisprudence in an increasingly globalized world.</p>
                    
                    <p>This event is particularly relevant for graduate students interested in Islamic law, contemporary religious thought, and the intersection of tradition and modernity in Islamic scholarship.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="speaker-info">
                    <div class="speaker-photo">
                        <img src="../photos/speaker1.jpg" alt="Dr. Ayatollah Syed Muhammad Rizvi" />
                    </div>
                    <h3>Dr. Ayatollah Syed Muhammad Rizvi</h3>
                    <p><strong>Senior Research Fellow in Islamic Law</strong><br>
                    University of Oxford</p>
                    
                    <p>Dr. Rizvi is a renowned scholar of Shii jurisprudence with over 20 years of experience in Islamic legal studies. He completed his hawza studies in Qum and holds a PhD from Harvard University. His research focuses on the methodology of Islamic law and its application to contemporary issues.</p>
                    
                    <p>He has published extensively on topics including bioethics in Islamic law, environmental jurisprudence, and the role of reason in Shii legal methodology. His most recent book, "Modern Applications of Classical Principles" (2023), examines how traditional Islamic legal principles can be applied to contemporary challenges.</p>
                    
                    <p>Dr. Rizvi currently serves as a Senior Research Fellow at the Centre for Islamic Studies at Oxford and is a frequent contributor to international conferences on Islamic law and ethics.</p>
                </div>
